Law of love?  Sounds good so, tell me more
Love of law?  mmmmaybenot so sure
You can disregard the ancients 
label them  Not Applicable  bin that bulky file
or try to get some sense; and they say
that love and law are so close intertwined
that together, they can know
more than each other taken individually.
What can this do? Where can we begin?
Those philosophers believe that all this universe,
all this creation, is one single act of love;
love draws it forth, destroys it, protects it,
and so eventually, it descends into passion;
and by the rules of love,
which hold all forms by law,
our natural state is naught but love;
and knowing this, feels no injustice in ourself;
understands all as equal; understands no constraints nor compulsions;
understands no darkness; and no prejudice or preferentiality;
and partaking of this universal love,
were so just, and light of heart,
and eager of response..
and so, this love, which understands ourself as love,
(for this creature's essence is pure love)
will love the rules which do our nature so;
love the rules of love, and live as love;
so out of love, goes law;
and out of law, goes love.
only in this fleeting time of the present
is our happiness lived;
and only if, in this continuous now,
love and law are present in each action,
can we make our golden future;
live a golden lifetime, where law has made me free.
this, the philosophers believe; the proof is ours to live.
